<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99850503731961></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99850503731961><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99850503731961>RE: Endevor</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99850503731961#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 22nd 2:30 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Basic rule for stacking questions is this: If it has a buffing icon, like, say, Anthem, then it will not stack with multiple bards. It is an effect, like any other buff, just with a short duration. Just like you can't stack a shammy str buff with the same one from another shammy. The mana song "stacks" because it isn't a buff or effect. Every time you play it i.e. every time you get the message "Your mind clears" it restores a bit of mana. It is instant, rather than an effect. It gives the illusion of being a stacked buff if multiple bard play it, though the real effect is just more bards hitting the party every three seconds or so with an instant mana regen, so even then, it isn't really stacking.<br><br>Cidol Wrathdealer<br>35 Bard of Karana<br>Drinal<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
