	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a lvl 40 bard on Veeshan atm, i know it is quite easy for a bard to solo. I suggest that anyone who wishes to start a bard should get used to soloing. Once you get to lvl 20 soloing becomes very easy because of the snare song. Kiting is quite easy and the exp is worth it... and if you get SoW, you dont need to bother snaring the enemy or twisting selos and damage songs to kite, with SoW you can use 3 damage songs which has, for me, decreased kiting time almost in half. Also you should focus on getting the best instrument for you kiting... for me percussion instruments are the best considering the Fufil's DoT and Chant of Flame are increased with percussion instruments... one song can do an extra 50 damage during its existance, and when you hafta twist the songs repeatedly, this saves you much time which can be used getting more exp. And as most of you know, bards only get dual wield, tho this seems unfair i know from experience that if you are fighting an enemy and you twist 3 damage songs while using 2 decent weapons, you can do alot of damage. Being a lucky bastard, i have a symphonic saber (11 23 10cha 5int effect: symphonic harmony) and a yak.. i cannot deal out rogue and monk damage but i can usually do close to 900 damage on a mob with 3k hp. This is just my advice, it works for me and once you become good with a bard, you can almost solo anything thats your lvl or below.<br><br>Codary Floats<br>40 Bard<br>Veeshan<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
